   "source": [
    "## Data Cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "Market capitalisation is computed as shares outstanding times absolute price, expressed in millions of USD. Observations with missing returns or market capitalisation are excluded from the sample. Excess returns are clipped at $-100\\%$ to remove data errors in CRSP raw returns. Lagged market capitalisation (one month) is used as portfolio weights to ensure all weighting variables are known at the time of portfolio formation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "00d39c79",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#| eval: false\n",
    "# Lagged market cap (one month) for portfolio weighting — computed from raw download\n",
    "mktcap_lag = (\n",
    "    crsp_monthly\n",
    "    .assign(\n",
    "        mktcap=lambda x: (x[\"shrout\"] * x[\"altprc\"].abs() / 1_000_000).replace(0, np.nan),\n",
    "        date=lambda x: x[\"date\"] + pd.DateOffset(months=1)\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    .rename(columns={\"mktcap\": \"mktcap_lag\"})\n",
    "    [[\"permno\", \"date\", \"mktcap_lag\"]]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute market cap, merge lag, compute excess returns\n",
    "crsp_monthly = (\n",
    "    crsp_monthly\n",
    "    .assign(mktcap=lambda x: (x[\"shrout\"] * x[\"altprc\"].abs() / 1_000_000).replace(0, np.nan))\n",
    "    .merge(mktcap_lag, how=\"left\", on=[\"permno\", \"date\"])\n",
    "    .merge(factors_ff3_monthly[[\"date\", \"risk_free\"]], how=\"left\", on=\"date\")\n",
    "    .assign(ret_excess=lambda x: (x[\"ret\"] - x[\"risk_free\"]).clip(lower=-1))\n",
    "    .drop(columns=[\"risk_free\"])\n",
    "    .dropna(subset=[\"ret_excess\", \"mktcap\", \"mktcap_lag\"])\n",
    "    [[\"permno\", \"date\", \"ret\", \"ret_excess\", \"mktcap\", \"mktcap_lag\", \"exchange\"]]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "crsp_monthly.to_parquet(\"data/crsp_monthly.parquet\")"
   ]
