    "## Daily CRSP Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Beta estimation in Frazzini and Pedersen (2014)[@frazzinipedersen2014] requires daily returns. The volatility component of beta uses a 1-year rolling window (252 trading days, minimum 120 observations) of daily excess returns. We also retain bid and ask prices from CRSP to compute proportional half-spreads for the transaction cost analysis. We download the daily data in batches of 500 PERMNOs to manage memory."
   ]
